CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 28, 1961, pg. A4 reads: "Gifts From Eastern Star - To further aide in the sound development of youths in this area, the Deborah Grand Chapter of the Order of the Eastern Star recently gave two sets of gifts to the Kay Boys Club...The right photo shows Lawrence Thrift of 1810 Webster Ave. and Charles Bowles of 8 Monaca Place, who gave Mrs. Tucker and G.E. Matthews, Kay staff member, a demonstration on one of two game tables which the Eastern Star gave to the club. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Ruth Tucker and G.E. Matthews watching Lawrence Thrift and Charles Bowles playing bumper pool in Kay Boys Club
